s:2:\"ro\";s:7:\"created\";s:10:\"1310598658\";s:7:\"changed\";s:10:\"1348589920\";s:4:\"tnid\";s:1:\"0\";s:9:\"translate\";s:1:\"0\";s:18:\"revision_timestamp\";s:10:\"1348589920\";s:12:\"revision_uid\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";a:2:{s:2:\"en\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:5:\"value\";s:1831:\"<p>Between 22 and 26 of August 2011 I will attend&nbsp;<a fcksavedurl=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\" href=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\">Drupalcon London 2011</a>. I&#39;m returning to London after 12 years. This time I&#39;m joining the (already) famous biannual event of a great community of enthusiasts and professionals: The Drupal Community.</p>\r\n<p>Drupalcon is an international event that brings together those who use, develop, design and support the Drupal platform.&nbsp;<a fcksavedurl=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\" href=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\">Drupalcon London 2011</a>&nbsp;will host dozens of sessions and panels from some of the most influential people and brightest minds within the Drupal community and beyond. The conference was always the opportunity for networking, informal coversations and contributions to Drupal.</p>\r\n<p>Drupalcon (Drupal Conference) takes place twice a year. It is already a widely accepted that the spring edition is taking place in the United States and the one in the late summer, on the Old Europe continent. I have not missed any of the last edition of the European Drupalcon:<a fcksavedurl=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/13956390@N06/2810680146/\" href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/13956390@N06/2810680146/\">Szeged, Paris,&nbsp;</a><a fcksavedurl=\"http://www.claudiucristea.ro/2010/08/something-happens-in-the-state-of-denmark\" href=\"http://www.claudiucristea.ro/2010/08/something-happens-in-the-state-of-denmark\">Copenhagen</a>. I&#39;ll be in London as president and founder of the&nbsp;<a fcksavedurl=\"http://drupal.org.ro/\" href=\"http://drupal.org.ro/\">Drupal Romania Association</a>&nbsp;and as managing partner and developer in&nbsp;<a fcksavedurl=\"http://webikon.com/\" href=\"http://webikon.com/\">Webikon</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Crossing the street in London? Watch right!</p>\r\n\";s:7:\"summary\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"format\";s:13:\"filtered_html\";s:10:\"safe_value\";s:1787:\"<p>Between 22 and 26 of August 2011 I will attend <a fcksavedurl=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\" href=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\">Drupalcon London 2011</a>. I\'m returning to London after 12 years. This time I\'m joining the (already) famous biannual event of a great community of enthusiasts and professionals: The Drupal Community.</p>\n<p>Drupalcon is an international event that brings together those who use, develop, design and support the Drupal platform. <a fcksavedurl=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\" href=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\">Drupalcon London 2011</a> will host dozens of sessions and panels from some of the most influential people and brightest minds within the Drupal community and beyond. The conference was always the opportunity for networking, informal coversations and contributions to Drupal.</p>\n<p>Drupalcon (Drupal Conference) takes place twice a year. It is already a widely accepted that the spring edition is taking place in the United States and the one in the late summer, on the Old Europe continent. I have not missed any of the last edition of the European Drupalcon:<a fcksavedurl=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/13956390@N06/2810680146/\" href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/13956390@N06/2810680146/\">Szeged, Paris, </a><a fcksavedurl=\"http://www.claudiucristea.ro/2010/08/something-happens-in-the-state-of-denmark\" href=\"http://www.claudiucristea.ro/2010/08/something-happens-in-the-state-of-denmark\">Copenhagen</a>. I\'ll be in London as president and founder of the <a fcksavedurl=\"http://drupal.org.ro/\" href=\"http://drupal.org.ro/\">Drupal Romania Association</a> and as managing partner and developer in <a fcksavedurl=\"http://webikon.com/\" href=\"http://webikon.com/\">Webikon</a>.</p>\n<p>Crossing the street in London? Watch right!</p>\n\";s:12:\"safe_summary\";s:0:\"\";}}s:2:\"ro\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:5:\"value\";s:2029:\"<p>&Icirc;ntre 22 și 26 august 2011 voi participa la&nbsp;<a fcksavedurl=\"http://london2011.drupal.org\" href=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\">Drupalcon London 2011</a>. Mă &icirc;ntorc la Londra după 12 ani. De data asta la (deja) celebrul eveniment bianual al unei comunități de entuziaști și profesioniști din care fac și eu parte: Comunitatea Drupal.</p>\r\n<p>Drupalcon este un eveniment internațional care reunește pe cei care folosesc, dezvoltă, proiectează și susțin platforma&nbsp;<a fcksavedurl=\"http://drupal.org\" href=\"http://drupal.org/\">Drupal.&nbsp;</a><a fcksavedurl=\"http://london2011.drupal.org\" href=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\">Drupalcon London 2011</a>&nbsp;va găzdui zeci de sesiuni și panel-uri susținute de unele dintre cele mai influente și mai strălucite minți din comunitatea Drupal (...and beyond). Conferința a fost dintotdeauna oportunitatea numărul 1 &icirc;n realizarea de parteneriate, dialoguri informale și contribuții la Drupal.</p>\r\n<p>Drupalcon (Conferința Drupal) se desfășoară de două ori pe an. Este deja o cutumă larg acceptată ca ediția de primăvară să se desfășoare &icirc;n Statele Unite iar cea de la finele verii să fie găzduită pe bătr&acirc;nul continent. Nu am lipsit la nici una din ultimele ediții europene ale Drupalcon:&nbsp;<a fcksavedurl=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/13956390@N06/2810680146/\" href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/13956390@N06/2810680146/\">Szeged</a>, Paris,&nbsp;<a fcksavedurl=\"http://www.claudiucristea.ro/2010/08/something-happens-in-the-state-of-denmark\" href=\"http://www.claudiucristea.ro/2010/08/something-happens-in-the-state-of-denmark\">Copenhaga</a>. Voi fi la Londra ca și președinte și fondator al&nbsp;<a fcksavedurl=\"http://drupal.org.ro\" href=\"http://drupal.org.ro/\">Asociației Drupal Rom&acirc;nia</a>&nbsp;dar și ca asociat și dezvoltator &icirc;n cadrul&nbsp;<a fcksavedurl=\"http://webikon.com\" href=\"http://webikon.com/\">Webikon</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Crossing the street in London? Watch right!</p>\r\n\";s:7:\"summary\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"format\";s:13:\"filtered_html\";s:10:\"safe_value\";s:1954:\"<p>Între 22 și 26 august 2011 voi participa la <a fcksavedurl=\"http://london2011.drupal.org\" href=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\">Drupalcon London 2011</a>. Mă întorc la Londra după 12 ani. De data asta la (deja) celebrul eveniment bianual al unei comunități de entuziaști și profesioniști din care fac și eu parte: Comunitatea Drupal.</p>\n<p>Drupalcon este un eveniment internațional care reunește pe cei care folosesc, dezvoltă, proiectează și susțin platforma <a fcksavedurl=\"http://drupal.org\" href=\"http://drupal.org/\">Drupal. </a><a fcksavedurl=\"http://london2011.drupal.org\" href=\"http://london2011.drupal.org/\">Drupalcon London 2011</a> va găzdui zeci de sesiuni și panel-uri susținute de unele dintre cele mai influente și mai strălucite minți din comunitatea Drupal (...and beyond). Conferința a fost dintotdeauna oportunitatea numărul 1 în realizarea de parteneriate, dialoguri informale și contribuții la Drupal.</p>\n<p>Drupalcon (Conferința Drupal) se desfășoară de două ori pe an. Este deja o cutumă larg acceptată ca ediția de primăvară să se desfășoare în Statele Unite iar cea de la finele verii să fie găzduită pe bătrânul continent. Nu am lipsit la nici una din ultimele ediții europene ale Drupalcon: <a fcksavedurl=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/13956390@N06/2810680146/\" href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/13956390@N06/2810680146/\">Szeged</a>, Paris, <a fcksavedurl=\"http://www.claudiucristea.ro/2010/08/something-happens-in-the-state-of-denmark\" href=\"http://www.claudiucristea.ro/2010/08/something-happens-in-the-state-of-denmark\">Copenhaga</a>. Voi fi la Londra ca și președinte și fondator al <a fcksavedurl=\"http://drupal.org.ro\" href=\"http://drupal.org.ro/\">Asociației Drupal România</a> dar și ca asociat și dezvoltator în cadrul <a fcksavedurl=\"http://webikon.com\" href=\"http://webikon.com/\">Webikon</a>.</p>\n<p>Crossing the street in London? Watch right!</p>\n\";s:12:\"safe_summary\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:10:\"field_tags\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:2:{i:0;a:1:{s:3:\"tid\";s:2:\"10\";}i:1;a:1:{s:3:\"tid\";s:2:\"11\";}}}s:16:\"field_main_image\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:13:{s:3:\"fid\";s:2:\"22\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"1\";s:8:\"filename\";s:24:\"beatles_-_abbey_road.jpg\";s:3:\"uri\";s:33:\"public://beatles_-_abbey_road.jpg\";s:8:\"filemime\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:8:\"filesize\";s:6:\"113868\";s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"timestamp\";s:10:\"1348589920\";s:11:\"rdf_mapping\";a:0:{}s:3:\"alt\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"width\";s:3:\"700\";s:6:\"height\";s:3:\"479\";}}}s:12:\"field_images\";a:0:{}s:11:\"title_field\";a:2:{s:2:\"ro\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"value\";s:35:\"Drupalcon Londra 2011. Watch right!\";s:6:\"format\";N;s:10:\"safe_value\";s:35:\"Drupalcon Londra 2011. Watch right!\";}}s:2:\"en\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"value\";s:35:\"Drupalcon Londra 2011. Watch right!\";s:6:\"format\";N;s:10:\"safe_value\";s:35:\"Drupalcon Londra 2011. Watch right!\";}}}s:22:\"field_main_image_style\";a:1:{s:3:\"und\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:5:\"value\";s:10:\"full-image\";}}}s:14:\"title_original\";s:35:\"Drupalcon Londra 2011. Watch right!\";s:12:\"translations\";O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:8:\"original\";s:2:\"ro\";s:4:\"data\";a:2:{s:2:\"ro\";a:9:{s:11:\"entity_type\";s:4:\"node\";s:9:\"entity_id\";s:2:\"13\";s:8:\"language\";s:2:\"ro\";s:6:\"source\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"1\";s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"translate\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"created\";s:10:\"1348555892\";s:7:\"changed\";s:10:\"1348555892\";}s:2:\"en\";a:9:{s:11:\"entity_type\";s:4:\"node\";s:9:\"entity_id\";s:2:\"13\";s:8:\"language\";s:2:\"en\";s:6:\"source\";s:2:\"ro\";s:3:\"uid\";s:1:\"1\";s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"translate\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"created\";s:10:\"1348555943\";s:7:\"changed\";s:10:\"1348556235\";}}}s:11:\"rdf